  "message": "test(fuzz/raptorq_envelope_decrypt): add seeds for 2 missing tamper branches (br-atva7)\n\nCloses flywheel_connectors-atva7.\n\nReviewer (cod_2) flagged that fuzz_targets/raptorq_envelope_decrypt.rs\ndeclares CiphertextTruncate (line 35, arm :166-172) and ObjectIdBitflip\n(line 37, arm :177-179) mutation paths, but the checked-in corpus only\nships identity_chacha.json + 8 tamper seeds (auth_tag, ciphertext,\nepoch_id, esi, frame_seq, k, sender_instance_id, wrong_zone_key).\n\nShort smoke runs only exercise the checked-in corpus, so two negative-\nauthentication branches the harness CLAIMS to cover were never\nactually hit by the seed set \u2014 regressions in ciphertext truncation or\nobject-id AAD binding could land unnoticed.\n\nFix: add two deterministic seeds matching the existing corpus style\n(per-seed byte-fill pattern for key_seed/zone_key_id/object_id):\n\n- tamper_ciphertext_truncate.json: ChaCha20Poly1305, mutation_index=0\n  (non-empty plaintext so the truncate arm hits the else branch); k=5,\n  esi=11, plaintext_len=128.\n- tamper_object_id.json: XChaCha20Poly1305, mutation_index=19\n  (non-boundary byte inside the 32-byte ObjectId); k=6, esi=12,\n  plaintext_len=112.\n\nSmoke verified: cargo +nightly fuzz run fuzz_raptorq_envelope_decrypt\n-- -max_total_time=40 against the full corpus dir \u2014 278253 runs in 41s\n(~6885 exec/s), no crashes, both new seeds parsed and executed.\n\nCod_4 / SunnyMoose",
